# Nootropix Design System

## Brand Colors

All colors are CSS custom properties stored as RGB triplets, consumed via `rgba(var(--color-*))` or `color-mix()`.

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| `--color-accent` | `#fbbf24` | Primary gold ŌĆö CTAs, links, highlights |
| `--color-accent-2` | `#f8c500` | Gold alternate |
| `--color-foreground` | `#1e1e1e` | Body text, headings |
| `--color-foreground-3` | `#666666` | Muted/secondary text |
| `--color-background` | `#ffffff` | Page background |
| `--color-background-2` | `#f6f6f6` | Secondary backgrounds |
| `--color-error` | `#da1e28` | Errors, sale badges |
| `--color-success` | `#10a71f` | Success, "new" badges |

IMPORTANT: Never hardcode hex colors. Always use `rgba(var(--color-*))` or `color-mix(in srgb, rgba(var(--color-foreground)) <opacity>, transparent)`.

### Color Schemes

Six schemes defined in `settings_data.json`, all pivoting around amber/gold accent:

- `background-1` ŌĆö Primary light (white bg, gold accent, dark text)
- `background-2` ŌĆö With gradient overlay
- `inverse` ŌĆö Light gray bg, inverted text
- Two custom schemes ŌĆö Gold-heavy variants
- `scheme-premium-health` ŌĆö Green CTA (`#5a9d6f`) on light gray

Apply via class `color-{{ scheme }}` on section containers.

