### Contrast Check

Body text uses `--font-body-color-opacity: 0.75` which reduces effective contrast. When generating components with opacity-reduced text, verify the result still meets WCAG AA: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text (18px+) and non-text elements like borders and icons.

## Typography

- Font: **Inter** for both body (weight 400) and headings (weight 600 / SemiBold)
- Body: `1.5rem` mobile, `1.6rem` desktop, `0.75` opacity via `--font-body-color-opacity`
- Headings: large with tight negative `letter-spacing`, line-height `1.3`
- Fluid sizing via `clamp()` between viewport range 400pxŌĆō1200px

| Level | Scale | Mobile | Desktop 768px+ | Large 1400px+ |
|-------|-------|--------|----------------|---------------|
| H1 | 1.2 | ~53px | ~90px | ~120px |
| H2 | 1.1 | ~40px | ~66px | ~83px |
| H3 | 1.05 | ~34px | ~53px | ~63px |
| H4 | 1.0 | 25px | 42px | 50px |
| H5 | 1.0 | 24px | 31px | 42px |
| H6 | 1.0 | 18px | 24px | 31px |

