## Animations

- Entrance: `fade-up`, `500ms`, scroll-triggered via `<xo-animate>`
- Modals: `zoom`, `300ms`, decay easing
- Drawers: `400ms`, decay easing
- CSS transitions: fast `0.2s ease`, medium `0.3s ease-in-out`, signature `0.5s cubic-bezier(.25,.74,.22,.99)`
- Named easings: `--out-soft`, `--spring`, `--out-cubic`, `--in-out-quart` (14 total in `styles.css`)
- IMPORTANT: Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` in all new animation code

## Performance

IMPORTANT: Shopify's guiding principle is to build primarily with HTML and CSS, using JavaScript only as progressive enhancement.

- Prefer HTML/CSS solutions over JavaScript for new components
- Reuse existing `xo-*` web components rather than writing new JS from scratch
- Keep new JS minimal ŌĆö Shopify auto-minifies, but bundles should stay lean (target <16KB per file)
- Use `loading="lazy"` on images below the fold; `loading="eager"` + `fetchpriority="high"` only for first viewport
- No Sass/.scss files ŌĆö only native `.css` files in `assets/`
- Avoid third-party frameworks and large utility libraries
- Wrap JS in function scopes (IIFE) to prevent namespace collisions
